<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.IFrameBuffer.DefineViewportRegion" Title="DefineViewportRegion method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IFrameBuffer">IFrameBuffer</PageRef> ->
    DefineViewportRegion
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>DefineViewportRegion</TypeRef> method defines the position and size of the viewport to draw into within the bound texture or window.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[void DefineViewportRegion(const V2UInt32& startPos, const V2UInt32& size);]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Argument list">
      <ArgumentList>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="const V2UInt32" Name="startPos">
          The top-left pixel position of the viewport rectangle.
        </ArgumentListEntry>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="const V2UInt32" Name="size">
          The pixel dimensions of the viewport rectangle.
        </ArgumentListEntry>
      </ArgumentList>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="See also">
